constructor.details: Sets up the factory with meta-transaction support

params.forwarder: The address of the trusted forwarder for meta-transactions

create(string,string,uint8,uint48).details: Uses CREATE2 for deterministic addresses, includes reentrancy protection, and validates that the predicted address hasn't been used before.

params.collateralLivenessSeconds: Duration in seconds that collateral proofs remain valid (must be > 0)
params.decimals: The number of decimals for the token (must be <= 18)
params.name: The name of the token (e.g., "USD Stablecoin")

returns.token: The address of the newly created token

isAddressDeployed(address).details: Returns true if the address was created by this factory, false otherwise

returns._0: True if the address was created by this factory, false otherwise

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

predictAddress(address,string,string,uin.details: Calculates the deterministic address using CREATE2 with the same parameters and salt computation as the create function. This allows users to know the token's address before deployment.

params.collateralLivenessSeconds: Duration in seconds that collateral proofs remain valid
params.decimals: The number of decimals for the token
params.name: The name of the token
params.sender: The address that would create the token

returns.predicted: The address where the token would be deployed

trustedForwarder().details: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder.

create(string,string,uint8,uint48).notice: Creates a new stablecoin token with the specified parameters

isAddressDeployed(address).notice: Checks if an address was deployed by this factory

isFactoryToken(address).notice: Mapping to track if an address was deployed by this factory

predictAddress(address,string,string,uin.notice: Predicts the address where a token would be deployed
